---
<Layout title="Leonardo Castro Web oficial, portafolio y CV">
    <main class="box mx-auto px-4">
        <!-- header -->
        <header class="pt-16 md:pt-24">
            <div class="flex max-[320px]:flex-col justify-start min-[321px]:justify-between min-[321]:items-center border border-[#a9b4c6] border-dashed">
                <img class="max-[467px]:w-[100px] max-w-[180px] border-r border-[#a9b4c6] border-dashed" src="/assets/media/images/profile.webp" alt="foto de perfil de Leonardo Castro">
                <div class="flex-grow p-4 border-[#a9b4c6] border-dashed header-border-fix">
                    <h1 class="max-[468px]:text-xs text-lg md:text-xl font-bold">Leonardo Daniel Castro Morales</h1>
                    <h2 class="max-[468px]:text-xs text-md md:text-lg">Backend & Systems Engineer — designing explicit, domain-driven software in Go.</h2>
                    <h3 class="max-[468px]:text-xs text-md md:text-lg space-x-2 min-[420px]:pt-2">
                        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ldcmleo" class="hover:text-teal-600"><i class="nf nf-dev-linkedin"></i> Linkedin</a>
                        <a href="https://github.com/ldcmleo" class="hover:text-teal-600"><i class="nf nf-cod-github"></i> Github</a>
                    </h3>
                </div>
            </div>
        </header>
        <section class="border-x border-[#a9b4c6] border-dashed">
            <div class="relative">
                <div class="bg-square"></div>
                <h1 class="text-4xl pt-16 px-4 pb-4 border-b border-[#a9b4c6] border-dashed">About me</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-4 p-4">
                <p>I’m a backend and systems engineer focused on designing software that is clear, explicit, and aligned with real-world business rules. I primarily work with Go, building services where the domain drives the architecture, not the other way around.</p>
                <p>I specialize in modeling complex problems such as access control, usage rights over time, pricing rules, authentication flows, and operational processes. I tend to favor simple, explicit designs over opaque abstractions, aiming for systems that can be understood, maintained, and evolved by the teams that operate them.</p>
                <p>I frequently apply principles from Domain-Driven Design, not as a dogma, but as a practical tool to reduce ambiguity and make software reflect reality more accurately.</p>
                <p>A significant part of my work is developed as open-source software. This is not only a technical choice, but a conscious position: I believe systems should be auditable, sovereign, and controllable by the people who depend on them. I’m particularly interested in backend systems that work reliably in production without relying on unnecessary black boxes.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="border-x border-t border-[#a9d4c6] border-dashed">
            <div class="relative">
                <div class="bg-square"></div>
                <h1 class="text-4xl pb-4 px-4 pt-16 border-b border-[#a9b4c6] border-dashed">Experience</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="">
            {
                ProjectsData.map((obj: any) => (
                    <Proyecto data={obj} client:load />
